Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Process mangoes in a food processor or blender until smooth. Set aside 1cup. Beat eggs at medium speed with an electric mixer until frothy; add SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, beating until blended. Gradually add cream,1 cup mango puree and vanilla, beating at low speed until blended. Pour custard mixture into 8 (6-ounce) custard cups. Set custard cups in a roasting pan; add hot water to a depth of 1 inch. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Remove custard cups from water. Serve custards at room temperature or chilled with mango slices and a dollop of whipped topping.